---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';

const updated = 'July 23, 2026';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Gargoyle Exterior Cleaning"
  description="How Gargoyle Exterior Cleaning collects, uses, and protects the information you share through this website."
>
  <section class="section section--flush">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="kicker">Privacy</p>
      <h1 class="display">Privacy policy.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        The short version: we only collect what we need to quote and do your
        job, we don't sell it, and we don't share it beyond the handful of
        services that keep this website and our email running.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="policy-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="body-copy" style="max-width: 44em;">
        <h2 id="policy-heading" class="title-md">What we collect</h2>
        <p>
          When you fill out the quote form on this site, we collect the
          information you enter — your name, phone number, email address,
          street address and city, the service you're interested in, and
          anything you write in the message field. If you call, text, or
          email us instead, we have whatever you choose to share that way.
        </p>

        <h2 class="title-md" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">Why we collect it</h2>
        <p>
          We use your information for one purpose: to respond to you, prepare
          a quote, schedule and complete your service, and stay in touch about
          that work. We don't sell your information, rent it, or hand it to
          anyone for advertising.
        </p>

        <h2 class="title-md" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">Who handles it</h2>
        <p>
          A few trusted services make this website and our communication work,
          and your information passes through them:
        </p>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>
            <strong>Netlify</strong> hosts this website and processes quote-form
            submissions, then emails them to us.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Google Workspace</strong> handles our business email, so
            our replies and your messages live there.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> gives us basic, anonymous
            visitor counts. It doesn't use cookies and doesn't track you as an
            individual across sites.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">
          Each of these has its own privacy practices, and we don't control how
          they operate beyond the service they provide us.
        </p>

        <h2 class="title-md" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">Cookies and tracking</h2>
        <p>
          This site doesn't set advertising or tracking cookies, and we don't
          run ad-network trackers on it. Our analytics are cookie-free.
        </p>

        <h2 class="title-md" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">How long we keep it</h2>
        <p>
          We hold onto quote requests and job records for as long as we need
          them to serve you and keep reasonable business records. If you'd like
          us to delete your information, just ask and we will, unless we're
          required to keep something for legal or tax reasons.
        </p>

        <h2 class="title-md" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">Your choices</h2>
        <p>
          You can ask us what information we have about you, ask us to correct
          it, or ask us to delete it. Reach out any time and we'll take care of
          it.
        </p>

        <h2 class="title-md" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">Questions</h2>
        <p>
          Email us at <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a> or call
          or text <a href={SITE.phoneHref}>{SITE.phone}</a> with anything about
          this policy or your information.
        </p>

        <p class="muted" style="margin-top: 2.5rem; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          Last updated {updated}. If we change how we handle your information,
          we'll update this page.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
